pliance with building code clause B1 =E2=80=93 Structure for timber framed =
buildings not requiring specific engineering design.&nbsp; This means that =
there is no legislative requirement for engaging a
 structural engineer for design requirements for the repair of this buildin=
g.&nbsp; As such, any repair or construction carried out in accordance with=
 the Standard is deemed to satisfy the relevant provisions of the building =
code and the Building Act 2004.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
